## Environment variables (`.env`)

| Variable             | Description                               |
| -------------------- | ----------------------------------------- |
| `OPENAI_EMAIL`       | Email used to sign into `chat.openai.com` |
| `OPENAI_PASSWORD`    | Password for that account                 |
| `OKX_API_KEY`        | OKX API key (trading enabled)             |
| `OKX_API_SECRET`     | OKX API secret                            |
| `OKX_API_PASSPHRASE` | OKX API passphrase                        |

## Usage

```text
$ python cli.py trade
Coin pair [autocomplete]: PEPE-USDT
Desired risk:reward [3.0]: 4
Order size (quote currency): 50
Leverage [1]: 10
Generating trade via ChatGPT...
{
  "side": "long",
  "entry": "0.00000825",
  "stop_loss": "0.00000777",
  "take_profit": "0.00001017",
  "rr": 4.2,
  "justification": "Bullish breakout from descending wedge + volume spike"
}
Place this order? [y/N]: y
Order placed:
{ ...OKX order response... }
```

## Logs

Each run appends a structured record to `trades.json` so you have an auditable trail.

## Caveats

- Browser selectors are brittle; if OpenAI changes its UI you may need to tweak `chatgpt_interface.py`.
